    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-02-02T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-02-02T03:00:00-05:00" n="765"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d765">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/1407: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Fish</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-02-02T10:00:00+02:00"
                            >February 2, 1939—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>10. Legation’s telegram No. 6, January 24, noon. It is confirmed by the British
                    Embassy that an agreement has been reached in principle whereby the Nashashibi
                    Party will be represented at the London Conference by means of delegates
                    selected by the party heads and the British.</p>
                <p>Reports that if the representatives of the Mufti withdrew as a protest against
                    the participation of the moderates then the latter will also retire leaving the
                    representation of the Arab cause to non-Palestinians are described at the
                    Embassy as “premature”. I presume that while such an understanding may have been
                    reached it is being stamped as a rumor pending the reaction of the Mufti. Its
                    apparent purpose is to serve notice that the British strongly desire all Arab
                    parties of Palestine to be represented but if that is impossible then it is
                    preferable that none should be.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fish</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
